title: San Fran-Caesar with Sour Dough Croutons
summary: Need a pescatarian side dish? San Fran-Caesar with Sour Dough Croutons could be an awesome recipe to try. This recipe serves 4. For $1.94 per serving, this recipe covers 19% of your daily requirements of vitamins and minerals. One serving contains 432 calories, 13g of protein, and 35g of fat. 10 people have made this recipe and would make it again. From preparation to the plate, this recipe takes roughly 30 minutes. A mixture of juice of lemon, dijon mustard, salt and coarse pepper, and a handful of other ingredients are all it takes to make this recipe so yummy. It is brought to you by Foodnetwork. With a spoonacular score of 63%, this dish is solid. Try San Fran-Caesar with Sour Dough Croutons, Chicken Caesar Salad with Garlic Croutons {and Light Caesar Dressing}, and Caesar Salad with Homemade Caesar Dressing and Croutons for similar recipes.
instructions: Preheat oven to 325 degrees F.                          Heat garlic and oil over low heat and melt butter into the oil. Place the bread in a large bowl and toss with garlic oil and butter. Season with pepper, Parmesan and thyme. Spread croutons evenly on a baking sheet and bake until crisp and golden, 15 minutes.                          In the bowl you made the croutons in, combine garlic, lemon juice, hot sauce, Worcestershire sauce and mustard. Whisk in extra-virgin olive oil while mixing the dressing.                          Remove croutons and let cool. When you are ready to serve, add lettuce to the dressing in the bowl and toss to coat evenly. Add cheese, salt and pepper, croutons. Toss again. Adjust seasonings and serve, with or without anchovies.

steps.step: Heat garlic and oil over low heat and melt butter into the oil.
Place the bread in a large bowl and toss with garlic oil and butter. Season with pepper, Parmesan and thyme.
Spread croutons evenly on a baking sheet and bake until crisp and golden, 15 minutes.
In the bowl you made the croutons in, combine garlic, lemon juice, hot sauce, Worcestershire sauce and mustard.
Whisk in extra-virgin olive oil while mixing the dressing.
Remove croutons and let cool. When you are ready to serve, add lettuce to the dressing in the bowl and toss to coat evenly.
Add cheese, salt and pepper, croutons. Toss again. Adjust seasonings and serve, with or without anchovies.
